snippet.textDisplay:
Now Coke Studio did justice to Bangladeshi music. We as Bangladeshi never recognise Nazrul's talent. Under the influence of Kolkata our own legend always remain unsung. Rabindronat is one of the greatest mind in bangla literature, no doubt. There are others how has soully given their whole life for Bangla. Under the influence of Robindronath and western midea of that time Nazrul never get the recognition that he deserved. Bangla speaking people as well as Bangladeshi we should have given appreciation to Nazrul.
I am a great admirer of Coke Studio because they bring out the real talent and give stage to every culture. But i get disappointed when instead of Bangladeshi it decided to keep the Bangla. I started to think that the only platform that could give our culture a exposure is getting influenced by the one section of bengali as always.
But so far it did a great job to represent Bangladesh. I hope to see more and more of bangla & bangladesh through Coke Studio.

Under the influence of Robindronath and western midea of that time Nazrul never get the recognition that he deserved. Bangla speaking people as well as Bangladeshi we should have given appreciation to Nazrul.
I am a great admirer of Coke Studio because they bring out the real talent and give stage to every culture. But i get disappointed when instead of Bangladeshi it decided to keep the Bangla. But so far it did a great job to represent Bangladesh. I hope to see more and more of bangla & bangladesh through Coke Studio.
